725628f-a.title: Queens: 73rd Avenue - 194th Street
725628f-a.text:
73rd Avenue, south side, at 194th Street, showing the
far boildinga and farm which was owned by P. Beadle in 1873
and J. Cline in 1891. In the latter year it was a 79-aore
farm. The view is east along the avenue, formerly Black Stump
Road, and the above location refers to where the farmhouses
are located.
P. L. Sperr  March 31, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS
